122
00:10:22,826 --> 00:10:25,021
I wouldn't listen to her chattering. 

123
00:10:25,391 --> 00:10:29,996
I would pay her back for all the 16 years
 when she wasn’t here on Mother's Day… 

124
00:10:30,212 --> 00:10:33,266
Nobody would be able to calm me down. 

125
00:10:33,581 --> 00:10:39,313
Maybe violence is not the best way out,
 but kicking her ass would make me feel better. 

126
00:10:39,659 --> 00:10:42,806
It'd be a miracle if I didn't kill her. 

127
00:10:48,927 --> 00:10:49,920
Good morning.

128
00:10:50,267 --> 00:10:52,267
Good morning. Come in, please.

129
00:10:54,025 --> 00:10:55,651
Forty one.

130
00:10:56,623 --> 00:11:03,545
Thirty four. Forty one. Here?

131
00:11:03,860 --> 00:11:04,744
Aha.

132
00:11:08,779 --> 00:11:10,245
Good morning. Can we come in?

133
00:11:10,409 --> 00:11:11,546
Come in, please.

134
00:11:11,845 --> 00:11:20,435
The father doesn't know where his wife is
 although he tried to find her. 

135
00:11:20,727 --> 00:11:25,334
Her friends refused to inform him where she is. 

136
00:11:25,740 --> 00:11:29,097
The father stopped drinking two years ago. 

137
00:11:29,197 --> 00:11:32,316
He is a member of Alcoholics Anonymous. 

138
00:11:33,173 --> 00:11:40,571
He believes other members of the AA group support him.

139
00:11:41,090 --> 00:11:43,883
The father seems to care for his daughters.

140
00:11:43,983 --> 00:11:47,834
Bożena Siankowska has been deprived of her parental rights.

141
00:11:48,133 --> 00:11:54,354
She isn't interested in her daughters and doesn't contact them.

142
00:11:59,039 --> 00:12:02,723
How come her ID number is not in the files? 

143
00:12:03,091 --> 00:12:05,801
What do you mean?

144
00:12:06,364 --> 00:12:10,550
You can change your place of residence, but not your ID number!

145
00:12:11,087 --> 00:12:13,479
Whose fault is it then?

146
00:12:13,684 --> 00:12:14,837
It's the court's fault. 

147
00:12:14,937 --> 00:12:16,491
They should have the basic data.

148
00:12:16,862 --> 00:12:19,531
You always want to have everything right away.

149
00:12:20,426 --> 00:12:23,165
Good morning. This is Bożena speaking. 

150
00:12:23,265 --> 00:12:25,003
Please leave the message.

151
00:12:31,631 --> 00:12:40,595
Hi, Mum. We're having a walk with Tola now. 

152
00:12:41,099 --> 00:12:44,516
We need to talk about our trip. 

153
00:12:44,616 --> 00:12:48,900
So, call me or I'll call you later. Bye.

154
00:12:50,654 --> 00:12:54,928
We've been in touch with her for only two weeks
 now and she wants to meet us now? 

155
00:12:55,279 --> 00:12:58,549
I don't even know this woman and
 I'm supposed to visit her abroad?

156
00:12:59,034 --> 00:13:03,101
It's more difficult for you because 
you don't even remember her. 

157
00:13:03,466 --> 00:13:08,135
She hasn't given us enough time
 to accept the fact that she’s with us again. 

158
00:13:08,580 --> 00:13:11,432
She wants to buy us one-way tickets. 

159
00:13:11,613 --> 00:13:14,538
We can come only if we have return tickets. 

160
00:13:14,751 --> 00:13:21,071
If we have return tickets and more time to think it over. 

161
00:13:21,171 --> 00:13:23,208
Not just two weeks.

162
00:13:24,160 --> 00:13:26,786
